document_data.Culture:
The majority of spellcasters pursued only one source of [[magic]], whether arcane or divine, but mystic theurges studied them both at once and blurred the lines between them. They drew their magical power from both faith in the [[god]]s and from [[spellbook]]s of arcane lore. Hence, mystic theurges were deeply interested in magic in all its forms. 

Mystic theurges were rare but not unknown within [[Waterdeep]]. They were common among [[human]]s of [[Halruaan (ethnicity)|Halruaan]] ancestry. [[Scro]] war priests were mystic theurges.{{Cite dragon/339/Races of Spelljammer|30-31}} 
[[Sharn]]s often were mystic theurges.
